commit.message:
Merge pull request #11 from mehak/master

Fixed two issues with Win.pm

Merge pull request #12 from rev112/master

Change deprecated *glob{FILEHANDLE} to *glob{IO}
Change deprecated *glob{FILEHANDLE} to *glob{IO}

Fix two issues: deprecated message and wrong type

- The arrow operator expects a reference to an array on the left side
when the right side contains [...].  Changing the @$ to just a plain
$ removes this error and returns the same value.

- The subroutine execute_complex_command in Unix.pm returns a refernce
to an array.  It seems like execute_complex_command in Win.pm should
do the same. (This was causing issues with parsing commands on
Windows 7).

Merge pull request #8 from rocky/master

Perl 5.16 deprecates defined(@array)

Merge pull request #7 from rocky/master

Possible fix for help not printing after the first time called.
Issue #6 - help was not showing anything after first time, because STDOUT was closed. Fix: dup'd STDOUT in the implementation of Psh::OS::display_pod
